HEADWORD: Relais
<hw>Re*lais"</hw> <pr>(r⟦eit⟧*l⟦asl⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
See <er>Relay</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A
narrow space between the foot of the rampart and the scarp of the ditch,
serving to receive the earth that may crumble off or be washed down, and
prevent its falling into the ditch.</def> <rj><au>Wilhelm.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

